The paper proposes a methodology to analyze cultural boundaries and similarities across populations based on Foursquare check-ins related to food and drink. This involves mapping check-ins to cultural preferences, identifying individual preferences and temporal habits, and using a clustering technique to draw cultural boundaries. This work involves social media analysis (cs.SI), computational social science (cs.CY), data mining (cs.SD), social networks (cs.SOC), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
